{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/styes-hordeola/diagnosis/assessment/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"d1fb36a8-3a50-5a20-b289-065601bca58a","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 96e79ba0-cbf2-49c7-a7e4-aad10101bb65 --><h2>How should I assess a person with a suspected stye?</h2><!-- end field 96e79ba0-cbf2-49c7-a7e4-aad10101bb65 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 02b45088-c2c4-44ea-a1cc-aad10101bb0f --><!-- begin field 8b8cc3cc-0b33-4ecf-bf4f-aad10101bb65 --><p><strong>If a person presents with a <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">suspected stye</a>:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Ask about:</strong><ul><li>Whether symptoms are unilateral or bilateral — symptoms are usually unilateral.</li><li>The timescale of symptoms — a stye typically develops over days.</li><li>Any previous episodes — recurrent styes in the same location may be a sign of an <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">alternative diagnosis</a>, including a malignant eyelid tumour (rare).</li><li>Any associated symptoms such as changes in visual acuity, double vision, limited or painful eye movements, or red eye, which may suggest an alternative diagnosis. Note: a stye should not affect visual acuity. See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/red-eye/\">Red eye</a> for more information.</li><li>Any triggers for symptoms, such as application of cosmetics, fragrances, haircare products, or contact lens use, which may suggest a diagnosis of contact dermatitis. See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/dermatitis-contact/\">Dermatitis - contact</a> for more information.</li><li>Any known co-morbidities or <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/background-information/risk-factors/\">risk factors</a> for the development of a stye, such as blepharitis or acne rosacea. See the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/\">Blepharitis</a> and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/rosacea/\">Rosacea - acne</a> for more information.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Examine the eye for:</strong><ul><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">Clinical features</a> of an external (swelling at the eyelid margin) or internal (swelling on the internal eyelid) stye. Note: it is important to evert the lower and upper eyelid during a full examination.</li><li>Clinical features suggesting a <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/background-information/complications/\">complication</a>, such as orbital or periorbital cellulitis, infective conjunctivitis, or a meibomian cyst (chalazion). See the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/cellulitis-acute/\">Cellulitis - acute</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/conjunctivitis-infective/\">Conjunctivitis - infective</a>, and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/meibomian-cyst-chalazion/\">Meibomian cyst (chalazion)</a> for more information.</li><li>Signs of chronic inflammation of surrounding skin (dryness, scaling, lichenification, and fissuring), which may suggest an <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">alternative diagnosis</a> such as eczema or blepharitis.</li><li>Any atypical clinical features, such as distortion of the eyelid margin, loss of eyelashes, ulceration, or bleeding, which may suggest an alternative diagnosis such as a <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">malignant eyelid tumour</a>.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 8b8cc3cc-0b33-4ecf-bf4f-aad10101bb65 --><!-- end item 02b45088-c2c4-44ea-a1cc-aad10101bb0f -->","topic":{"id":"cb7504e0-18ff-5b66-9a15-bdfffd57e4f2","topicId":"448c1307-bfa4-490c-9743-93410f0feab2","topicName":"Styes (hordeola)","slug":"styes-hordeola","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2019","chapters":[{"id":"b60f7b61-733c-5b26-aad2-a729543f9b6a","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"52930028-5a1d-5b9b-8d18-410218c68950","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ca563391-88ba-5cb3-acd3-b480ac60e6d5","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"be8f8436-fed4-575e-a868-64d29d17760b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"a96449f3-bc08-5678-9d20-b15129f23094","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"5c277a33-1ffb-5dab-8e93-4ae0a4a48e8e","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"c3857397-888b-57a9-a1f6-72a962d8eade","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"4b567870-85a5-52e0-927d-ab87e4f9f0b1","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"5213c038-99e5-5f7e-9984-ae5559ce3104","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"49e251c5-16d7-558e-b77a-a80aff716623","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"a8550c2a-2fc1-5741-80a6-743e1766f3df","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"18287988-0f32-5e2a-b30c-cd34c5e7b2fd","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"da56a858-c473-5def-8801-989cf80fa210","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"98551fd4-627b-517a-aba7-8656ba96ad0b","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"78602659-d6ff-56ee-adb7-0a51d96e86b3","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"d734ebf3-738b-536e-9473-8072dd641226","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"0e0153ae-adae-5a44-8468-b101d00dc192","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"5a804273-1412-54de-a3b5-25c8fa863f0c","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"0a8b467c-091a-58f5-9bbc-2e3d6e8b3050","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"d2097cac-14cf-521f-a880-bdd955383784","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"d1fb36a8-3a50-5a20-b289-065601bca58a","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"38039a14-5ba3-5ba7-9a1c-e3b65bfcc1f8","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"47ed49b0-38d1-564a-ba31-5832b9707b41","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"11a607c4-8726-5a1d-a7f5-2905c19fdd82","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"70575fa5-1365-5280-9b5f-9ebe8d134019","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"7a7274b0-4626-5ff4-9bce-54e5a161f348","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"32cb05b0-ad89-53a9-b26f-ef372f72f69e","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"4497b0ae-22a6-5f3c-8f1b-b780f7086f52","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"e326b7c0-a905-5837-9e07-341ea8b399f0","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"97440552-2037-50e3-be44-1f184916566f","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"486c965c-286d-5953-b87a-f6acdbc53165","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"85bed52c-544f-5f93-bbb8-7436c2036263","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"0a8b467c-091a-58f5-9bbc-2e3d6e8b3050","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"268af962-8275-56e7-a4ff-38b44f1beb48","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-bc4","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 2b2a5722-8228-41c0-bfd4-aad10101d5ab --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 2b2a5722-8228-41c0-bfd4-aad10101d5ab -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item bc4cff01-ac67-4d73-87bb-aad10101d582 --><!-- begin field 26864150-d45b-42e8-ba4e-aad10101d5ab --><p>The recommendations on the assessment of a suspected stye are based on expert opinion in review articles on eyelid conditions [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/references/\">Peralejo et al, 2008</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/references/\">Gupta et al, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/references/\">Carlisle, 2015</a>] and on other eye conditions [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/references/\">Mueller and McStay, 2008</a>].</p><ul><li>The information on potential triggers for contact dermatitis are based on expert opinion in a review article [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/references/\">Peralejo et al, 2008</a>].</li><li>The information about the potential significance of recurrent styes in the same location is based on expert opinion in a review article [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/references/\">Gupta et al, 2014</a>].</li><li>The recommendation to evert the upper and lower eyelid is based on the fact that lesions that appear small on initial inspection may have a large component hidden from direct view [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/styes-hordeola/references/\">Gupta et al, 2014</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 26864150-d45b-42e8-ba4e-aad10101d5ab --><!-- end item bc4cff01-ac67-4d73-87bb-aad10101d582 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}